# LLM Configuration
# =================

# Azure OpenAI models (gpt-5.1, gpt-4.1-mini, o3, gpt-image-1):
#   Authentication is automatic via DefaultAzureCredential (az login / VS Code / Managed Identity).
#   No API key needed — just ensure you have the "Cognitive Services OpenAI User" role
#   on the neo-models-swedencentral-azopenai-dev Azure OpenAI resource.
#   Contact your Azure administrator if you need the role assigned.

# Google Gemini models: coming soon

# Azure Document Intelligence (optional — for scanned/image PDFs)
# ================================================================
# Used automatically as fallback when PyMuPDF extracts < 4 000 characters.
# Set FORCE_DOC_INTELLIGENCE=true to always use it regardless of PyMuPDF output.
#
# RBAC required: "Cognitive Services User" role on the Document Intelligence resource.
#   az role assignment create \
#     --role "Cognitive Services User" \
#     --assignee <your-email-or-sp-id> \
#     --scope /subscriptions/<sub>/resourceGroups/<rg>/providers/Microsoft.CognitiveServices/accounts/<resource-name>
#
# AZURE_DOCUMENT_INTELLIGENCE_ENDPOINT=https://<your-resource>.cognitiveservices.azure.com/
# FORCE_DOC_INTELLIGENCE=false

# Azure OpenAI Whisper (optional — for audio transcription)
# ==========================================================
# Used by process_files.py to transcribe audio files (mp3, m4a, wav, ogg, webm).
# Requires an Azure OpenAI Whisper deployment.
#
# WHISPER_DEPLOYMENT_NAME=whisper
